-----------------------------------------------------
TERMINOLOGY
-----------------------------------------------------

	# Is a function that does NOT return a value 	#48
	  ie... Any function that ends with a STATEMENT
	  
	# Return type is inferred to be 'Unit' by the Compiler
	  
	# NOTE : Check old deprecated syntax 			#48
	
-----------------------------------------------------
EXAMPLE
-----------------------------------------------------

	scala> def log(d: Double) = println(f"Got value $d%.2f")
	log: (d: Double)Unit
	
	